Residents of Ng&rsquo;are Ng&rsquo;iro village, Laikipia East subcounty, yesterday protested against the killing of a 50-year-old man on Wednesday.Guard Edung Lopongo&rsquo;i was killed at the Segera Ranch by cattle rustlers. Police boss Zacchaeus Ng&rsquo;eno said armed herders stormed the ranch at night to relese cattle that were held for illegal grazing.He said the herders sprayed bullets on the two iron sheet houses where Lopongo&rsquo;i and six other guards were sleeping and one bullet hit him. He died at the ranch dispensary.&ldquo;They shot indiscriminately at the two houses, killing Lopongo&rsquo;i. They also left with 400 heads of cattle. The body was removed to Nanyuki Teaching and Referral Hospital mortuary,&rdquo; Ng&rsquo;eno said.